text.section:
The director shall have a practical knowledge of:
The different systems of working and ventilating coal mines;
The nature, chemistry, and properties of noxious, poisonous, and explosive gases, the dangers due to these gases, and the prevention of these dangers;
The dangers incident to blasting and the prevention of these dangers;
The methods for the management and extinguishment of mine fires;
The methods for rescue and relief work in mine disasters;
The application of electricity in mining operations;
The application of mechanical loading in mining operations;
The equipment and explosives manufactured for use in coal mines;
The methods used in locating oil and gas wells when drilled through any coal seam;
The proper manner of drilling and plugging oil and gas wells;
Mining engineering; and
The methods for the prevention of explosions in mines due to gas or dust.
